<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08396</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROMOTING THE PHILIPPINE FILM INDUSTRY THROUGH AN ANNUAL FILM QUOTA AND OTHER SUPPORT MEASURES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to safeguard the artistic and economic development of the film industry through an annual film quota that will require all cinemas and theatrical venues to exhibit only Filipino films for a period of twenty eight (28) days , from June 1 to June 14 and from December 18 to December 31. Seeks to guarantee all Filipino films a full week's run in all commercial theatres and booking priority on "payday playdates".</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-10-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Malapitan (000 2018-11-26)</td><td>2. Sandoval (000 2018-11-29)</td><tr><td>3. Olivarez (000 2018-12-04)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC INFORMATION ON 2018-10-10</td></tr></table>